The Hawks, police and Fisheries Department officials made the arrests during a raid. CAPE TOWN - Six people have been taken into custody following an abalone bust near Vredenburg.The Hawks, police and the Fisheries Department officials made the arrests during a raid on a farm yesterday morning.The Hawks' Lloyd Ramovha says the group is expected to appear in court today.&quot;The raid culminated in the arrest of six suspects, aged between 31 and 48, for running an illegal abalone facility. Equipment and abalone at an estimated value of over R2,5 million was seized.&quot;Two men were also arrested early this week in a dramatic bust near Somerset West. Perlemoen valued at around R2 million was also seized.